<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Administration - Subitems</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
  <xar:template type="module" module="subitems" file="admin-menu" />
  <img src="#xarTplGetImage('admin_generic.gif','base')#" class="xar-module-icon" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />

  <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>

  <h2><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>

      <p>
          <em><xar:mlstring>The Subitems module allows you to create and display subitems for any module item.</xar:mlstring></em>
      </p>
      <p><xar:mlstring>As an illustration of how subitems could be used</xar:mlstring>:
         <ul>
            <li><xar:mlstring>You may want a publication type (Articles pubtype) to hold 'cooking recipies'</xar:mlstring>
            <xar:mlstring>This pubtype should store and display additional recipe details such as ingredients and their quantity. Each recipe can contain a different number of ingredients.</xar:mlstring>
            <br />
            <xar:mlstring>A disadvantage of using the Dynamic Data module alone for this is the high number of ingredient fields needed to ensure that always enough fields are present. Furthermore all these input fields are always displayed.</xar:mlstring>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
      <p><xar:mlstring>The module author's intent was to produce a module which can be hooked from any other module and is able to both display and provide
            editing of subitems for an item. The design provides for one table which saves the subitem information with module/itemtype. A second table
            contains  the DD Itemids with corresponding module/itemtype/itemid in the DD object (1 to n Relation). 
            </xar:mlstring>
      </p>

  <a name="subitemshow"><h3><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></h3></a>
      <p>
          <ol>
            <li><xar:mlstring>Install the module (done by now, as you are seeing this page)</xar:mlstring> </li>
            <li>
                <xar:ml>
                <xar:mlstring>Go to <em>Admin - DynamicData - View Objects</em> and click <a href="#(1)">New Dynamic Object Item</a> to create a DD object.</xar:mlstring>
                <xar:mlvar>&xar-modurl-dynamicdata-admin-new;</xar:mlvar>
                </xar:ml>
            <xar:mlstring>This new dynamic data object will hold the subitem information.</xar:mlstring> 
            </li>
            <li><xar:mlstring>You are now in <em>Manage - View Dynamic Objects</em>. Click Edit on [YOUR OBJECT] at the bottom of the list. This displays the <em>Modify Item [YOUR ID] in Dynamic Objects</em> screen.</xar:mlstring></li>
            <li><xar:mlstring>Click <em>Modify Dynamic Properties</em> to add properties (fields) to the object. You <strong>must have</strong> at least one field with a Property Type of 'Item ID', Default of '0' and Status of 'Display Only'. Add further fields for the content you need.</xar:mlstring>
             </li>
           <li>
                <xar:ml>
                    <xar:mlstring>Go to <a href="#(1)">Admin - Subitems - Add Subitem Link</a>. Choose [YOUR OBJECT] and select the parent module and its itemtype that you will attach this property to.</xar:mlstring>
                    <xar:mlvar>&xar-modurl-subitems-admin-ddobjectlink_new;</xar:mlvar>
                </xar:ml>
            davor</li>
            <li>
                <xar:ml>
                    <xar:mlstring>Go to <a href="#(1)">Modules - Configure Hooks - Subitems</a> and enable the hook for the parent modules itemtype that you just created the link for.</xar:mlstring>
                    <xar:mlvar>
                        #xarModURL('modules', 'admin', 'hooks', array('hook'=>'subitems'), Null, 'currenthook')#
                    </xar:mlvar>
                </xar:ml>
            </li>
          </ol>
      </p>
      <p><xar:mlstring>That should be it (it has been tested with custom pubtypes)</xar:mlstring>.</p>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring></h3>
      <p> 
          <xar:mlstring>none</xar:mlstring>
      </p>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring></h3>
      <p>
          <ul>
              <li><xar:mlstring>new/create/modify/update/delete -- Allows you to create/update sub-items</xar:mlstring></li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>display -- Allows you to display sub-items</xar:mlstring></li>
          </ul>
      </p>
  <h3>
    <xar:mlstring>Further Information</xar:mlstring>
  </h3>
  <p>
    <xar:mlstring>Further information on the Subitems module can be found at</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Subitems Extension page at</xar:mlstring> <a title="#xarML('Subitems Module - Xaraya Extension 9356')#" href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/release/9356.html">Xaraya Extension and Releases</a>.
      <xar:mlstring> Click on Version History tab at the bottom to get the latest release information.</xar:mlstring>
    </li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Related tutorials and documentation on Subitems found at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/keywords/subitems/" title="#xarML('Related documentation on Subitems')#"><xar:mlstring>Xaraya Documentation.</xar:mlstring></a>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
